body:
Can we also add `no-useless-rename`? imo this should have been part of the recommended set since its inception. This isn't something that formatters like prettier would fix, so no conflict.

`no-useless-rename` is helpful when a symbol is renamed and can be `--fix`

```js
// BEFORE RENAME
const x = {foo: 42};
const {foo: bar} = x;

// AFTER RENAME
const x = {bar: 42};
const {bar: bar} = x;
```
